			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Shale oil is an unconventional oil produced from oil shale rock fragments by pyrolysis, hydrogenation, or thermal dissolution. These processes convert the organic matter within the rock into synthetic oil and gas. The resulting oil can be used immediately as a fuel or upgraded to meet refinery feedstock specifications. Shale oil is a high-quality crude oil that lies between layers of shale rock, impermeable mudstone, or siltstone. Oil companies produce shale oil by fracturing the rock formations that contain the layers of oil.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">页岩油是一种非常规油，由页岩岩石碎片通过裂解、加氢或热溶解产生。这些过程将岩石中的有机物转化为合成油和气体。得到的油可以立即用作燃料，或升级以满足炼油厂原料规格。页岩油是一种高质量的原油，位于页岩岩层、不透水的泥岩或粉砂岩层之间。石油公司通过压裂含有油层的岩石构造来生产页岩油。</common:generalComment>
